#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.78"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.78:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.78:0.2"
msgid "8. Apaṇṇakavagga "
msgstr "8. Guaranteed "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: dakkhiṇāvisuddhisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.78:0.3"
msgid "78. Dakkhiṇasutta "
msgstr "78. A Religious Donation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.78:1.1"
msgid "“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four ways of purifying a religious donation. "

msgctxt "an4.78:1.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.78:1.3"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato; "
msgstr "There’s a religious donation that’s purified by the giver, not the recipient. "

msgctxt "an4.78:1.4"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato; "
msgstr "There’s a religious donation that’s purified by the recipient, not the giver. "

msgctxt "an4.78:1.5"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato; "
msgstr "There’s a religious donation that’s purified by neither the giver nor the recipient. "

msgctxt "an4.78:1.6"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca. "
msgstr "There’s a religious donation that’s purified by both the giver and the recipient. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.81, sc2
msgctxt "an4.78:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato? "
msgstr "And how is a religious donation purified by the giver, not the recipient? "

#. VAR: paṭiggāhakā honti dussīlā pāpadhammā → paṭiggāhako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an4.78:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo; paṭiggāhakā honti dussīlā pāpadhammā. "
msgstr "It’s when the giver is ethical, of good character, but the recipient is unethical, of bad character. "

msgctxt "an4.78:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.78:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato? "
msgstr "And how is a religious donation purified by the recipient, not the giver? "

msgctxt "an4.78:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo; paṭiggāhakā honti sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā. "
msgstr "It’s when the giver is unethical, of bad character, but the recipient is ethical, of good character. "

msgctxt "an4.78:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā paṭiggāhakato visujjhati, no dāyakato. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.78:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato? "
msgstr "And how is a religious donation purified by neither the giver nor the recipient? "

msgctxt "an4.78:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti dussīlo pāpadhammo; paṭiggāhakāpi honti dussīlā pāpadhammā. "
msgstr "It’s when both the giver and the recipient are unethical, of bad character. "

msgctxt "an4.78:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā neva dāyakato visujjhati, no paṭiggāhakato. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.78:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca? "
msgstr "And how is a religious donation purified by both the giver and the recipient? "

msgctxt "an4.78:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, dāyako hoti sīlavā kalyāṇadhammo; paṭiggāhakāpi honti sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā. "
msgstr "It’s when both the giver and the recipient are ethical, of good character. "

msgctxt "an4.78:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, dakkhiṇā dāyakato ceva visujjhati paṭiggāhakato ca. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.78:5.4"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso dakkhiṇā visuddhiyo”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four ways of purifying a religious donation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.78:5.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
